name: Boxing Day
summary: On Boxing Day, Canadian shoppers flocked to stores to take advantage of sales amid ongoing cost-of-living pressures, bolstering business for some retailers but leaving smaller ones concerned about the impact of the challenging year. In Toronto, retailers reported a busy day but also noted that Boxing Day no longer carries the same weight as it once did. In Vancouver, crowds were anticipated at the airport and a shopping mall, while authorities urged travelers to plan ahead due to increased traffic. Regina offered family-friendly activities for the holiday. Both Toronto and Newfoundland experienced weather-related disruptions, with Toronto reporting closures and Avalon Peninsula under a snowfall warning. Meanwhile, travel deals and Amazon's Boxing Day sale offered additional savings opportunities.

name: Usman Khawaja
summary: Australian batsman Usman Khawaja has been the subject of media attention during the recent cricket test series between India and Australia. In one incident, he was criticized by fans for his reaction to Sam Konstas's celebration after dismissing a batsman. Another article highlights Jasprit Bumrah's shock at Khawaja's mistimed shot, which resulted in a catch for KL Rahul. Additionally, Khawaja's wife, Rachel, has spoken about the sacrifices involved in being a partner in a high-profile relationship. Khawaja has also commented on the overwhelming support for India during the Boxing Day test, and has teased Virat Kohli about his altercation with Konstas. Former Australian captain Michael Clarke has criticized selectors for dropping Nathan McSweeney in favor of Khawaja, who has been struggling for runs. In another incident, Khawaja was dismissed due to Mohammed Siraj's so-called "black magic." Despite these incidents, Khawaja has provided insights into the altercation between Kohli and Konstas at the MCG. On the first day of the fourth test, Konstas and Australia's top-order put their team in a strong position despite the efforts of Indian bowler Jasprit Bumrah.
